# Wonder UI Components

Use [@luckyluu/wonder-ui](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@luckyluu/wonder-ui) for UI primitives in KidStory. It is a kid-friendly design system (pastel colors, chunky 3D buttons, large tap targets) that fits this app.

## Setup

Ensure the package and global styles are loaded once at the app root:

```tsx
import '@luckyluu/wonder-ui/styles.css';
```

Load the Nunito font for intended typography:

```html
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Nunito:wght@400;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
```

## When to use

- **New buttons, inputs, cards, headings, text, badges, alerts, checkboxes, spinners** → use Wonder UI, not custom Tailwind equivalents.
- **Layout and page structure** → Tailwind utility classes are fine alongside Wonder UI.
- **Existing custom components** → do not rewrite unless the task explicitly asks for it.

## Imports

```tsx
import { Button, Card, Heading, Text, Input, Badge, Alert, Checkbox, Spinner } from '@luckyluu/wonder-ui';
```

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — Wonder UI for interactive UI
<Card variant="sky" header="Practice">
  <Heading level="h2">Flashcards</Heading>
  <Text>Tap a card to flip it.</Text>
  <Button variant="primary" onClick={onNext}>Next</Button>
</Card>

// ❌ BAD — custom styled button when Button exists
<button className="rounded-xl bg-blue-500 px-4 py-2 text-white">Next</button>
```

## Component reference

| Component | Notes |
|-----------|-------|
| `Button` | `primary`, `secondary`, `accent`, `ghost` |
| `Card` | `sky`, `butter`, `blush`, `mint` |
| `Input` | label, helper text, error state |
| `Heading` | `h1`–`h4` |
| `Text` | body copy; `muted` variant |
| `Badge`, `Alert`, `Checkbox`, `Spinner` | status, feedback, forms, loading |

Docs: https://luubinhan.github.io/wonder-ui/
